{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900310699,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be828d8001d7E4PF9BHIX6hn","messageID":"msg_d7be81289001KxTvTNH8FB0g66","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-025\n4: > **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n5: > **Language:** Python\n6: > **Size:** M\n7: > **Stage:** ST-1 (Initialized)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: The `MetadataService` class provides a unified, high-level interface for managing agent metadata and data models within the AgentCube CLI. This service abstracts storage operations, provides schema validation, versioning support, and enables agent discovery and configuration management.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-1.1 — Core Service Structure\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 1.1.1 | Create `MetadataService` class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | File exists with proper structure | 0.5h |\n22: | 1.1.2 | Define `MetadataStorage` abstract interface | Abstract base class with required methods | 0.5h |\n23: | 1.1.3 | Implement `__init__()` with storage injection | Storage interface properly initialized | 0.25h |\n24: | 1.1.4 | Add logging support with verbose mode | Logger configuration working | 0.25h |\n25: \n26: **Deliverable:** Core service structure defined.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## ST-1.2 — Data Model Definitions\n31: \n32: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n33: |---|------|--------------|------|\n34: | 1.2.1 | Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model | Model with all required fields | 0.5h |\n35: | 1.2.2 | Define `MetadataVersion` Pydantic model | Version tracking structure | 0.25h |\n36: | 1.2.3 | Add field validators for business rules | Custom validators implemented | 0.5h |\n37: | 1.2.4 | Define schema export functionality | JSON schema generation working | 0.25h |\n38: \n39: **Deliverable:** Data models defined with validation.\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## ST-1.3 — CRUD Operations Implementation\n44: \n45: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n46: |---|------|--------------|------|\n47: | 1.3.1 | Implement `create_metadata()` with validation | Returns created metadata with ID | 0.5h |\n48: | 1.3.2 | Implement `get_metadata()` by ID | Returns metadata or raises NotFound | 0.25h |\n49: | 1.3.3 | Implement `update_metadata()` with versioning | Version incremented on update | 0.5h |\n50: | 1.3.4 | Implement `delete_metadata()` soft delete | Marked as deleted, not removed | 0.25h |\n51: | 1.3.5 | Implement `list_metadata()` with pagination | Paginated results returned | 0.5h |\n52: \n53: **Deliverable:** CRUD operations functional.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## ST-1.4 — Search & Query Implementation\n58: \n59: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n60: |---|------|--------------|------|\n61: | 1.4.1 | Implement `search_metadata()` by keyword | Keyword search working | 0.5h |\n62: | 1.4.2 | Add filter by metadata type | Type filter returns correct results | 0.25h |\n63: | 1.4.3 | Add filter by status | Status filter working | 0.25h |\n64: | 1.4.4 | Add filter by tags | Tag-based filtering working | 0.25h |\n65: | 1.4.5 | Implement sorting options | Sort by created/updated/name | 0.25h |\n66: \n67: **Deliverable:** Search and query functional.\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## ST-1.5 — Import/Export Implementation\n72: \n73: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n74: |---|------|--------------|------|\n75: | 1.5.1 | Implement `export_metadata()` to JSON | JSON file created correctly | 0.5h |\n76: | 1.5.2 | Implement `import_metadata()` from JSON | Metadata imported with validation | 0.5h |\n77: | 1.5.3 | Handle import validation errors | Invalid data rejected with errors | 0.25h |\n78: | 1.5.4 | Support batch import/export | Multiple metadata handled | 0.25h |\n79: \n80: **Deliverable:** Import/export functional.\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## ST-1.6 — Error Handling & Exceptions\n85: \n86: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n87: |---|------|--------------|------|\n88: | 1.6.1 | Define `MetadataError` base exception | Base class implemented | 0.25h |\n89: | 1.6.2 | Define `MetadataNotFoundError` | Raised when ID not found | 0.25h |\n90: | 1.6.3 | Define `ValidationError` for schema errors | Schema validation errors | 0.25h |\n91: | 1.6.4 | Define `StorageError` for backend errors | Storage operation errors | 0.25h |\n92: \n93: **Deliverable:** Exception hierarchy defined.\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## ST-1.7 — Unit Tests — Core Service\n98: \n99: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n100: |---|------|--------------|------|\n101: | 1.7.1 | Write `TestMetadataServiceInit` — initialization | Service creates correctly | 0.5h |\n102: | 1.7.2 | Write `TestMetadataServiceCreate` — create operations | Create with validation tested | 0.5h |\n103: | 1.7.3 | Write `TestMetadataServiceRead` — read operations | Get by ID tested | 0.5h |\n104: | 1.7.4 | Write `TestMetadataServiceUpdate` — update with versioning | Version increment tested | 0.5h |\n105: | 1.7.5 | Write `TestMetadataServiceDelete` — soft delete | Delete marks as deleted | 0.5h |\n106: \n107: **Deliverable:** Core service tests pass with >80% coverage.\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## ST-1.8 — Unit Tests — Search & Validation\n112: \n113: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n114: |---|------|--------------|------|\n115: | 1.8.1 | Write `TestMetadataSearch` — keyword search | Search returns matches | 0.5h |\n116: | 1.8.2 | Write `TestMetadataFilters` — filter combinations | Multiple filters working | 0.5h |\n117: | 1.8.3 | Write `TestSchemaValidation` — valid data | Valid data passes | 0.5h |\n118: | 1.8.4 | Write `TestSchemaValidation` — invalid data | Invalid data rejected | 0.5h |\n119: | 1.8.5 | Write `TestImportExport` — roundtrip | Export then import works | 0.5h |\n120: \n121: **Deliverable:** Search and validation tests pass.\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## ST-1.9 — Integration Tests\n126: \n127: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n128: |---|------|--------------|------|\n129: | 1.9.1 | Create `tests/integration/test_metadata_service.py` | File with fixtures exists | 0.5h |\n130: | 1.9.2 | Test full CRUD lifecycle | Create → Read → Update → Delete | 1.0h |\n131: | 1.9.3 | Test search with real data | Search returns correct results | 0.5h |\n132: | 1.9.4 | Test import/export with files | File I/O works correctly | 0.5h |\n133: | 1.9.5 | Test error scenarios | Errors handled gracefully | 0.5h |\n134: \n135: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass.\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## ST-1.10 — Documentation\n140: \n141: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n142: |---|------|--------------|------|\n143: | 1.10.1 | Add module docstring to `metadata_service.py` | pydoc shows overview | 0.25h |\n144: | 1.10.2 | Add class docstring to `MetadataService` | Description and usage | 0.25h |\n145: | 1.10.3 | Add docstrings to all public methods | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n146: | 1.10.4 | Add type hints to all signatures | mypy passes without errors | 0.5h |\n147: \n148: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented.\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## ST-1.11 — Lint & Type Check\n153: \n154: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n155: |---|------|--------------|------|\n156: | 1.11.1 | Run `ruff check` on service files | No lint errors | 0.25h |\n157: | 1.11.2 | Run `mypy` on service files | No type errors | 0.25h |\n158: | 1.11.3 | Fix any ruff issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n159: | 1.11.4 | Fix any mypy issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n160: \n161: **Deliverable:** Code passes all checks.\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Summary\n166: \n167: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n168: |-------|-------|------------|\n169: | ST-1.1: Core Service Structure | 4 | 1.5h |\n170: | ST-1.2: Data Model Definitions | 4 | 1.5h |\n171: | ST-1.3: CRUD Operations | 5 | 2.0h |\n172: | ST-1.4: Search & Query | 5 | 1.5h |\n173: | ST-1.5: Import/Export | 4 | 1.5h |\n174: | ST-1.6: Error Handling | 4 | 1.0h |\n175: | ST-1.7: Unit Tests — Core | 5 | 2.5h |\n176: | ST-1.8: Unit Tests — Search | 5 | 2.5h |\n177: | ST-1.9: Integration Tests | 5 | 3.0h |\n178: | ST-1.10: Documentation | 4 | 1.5h |\n179: | ST-1.11: Lint & Type Check | 4 | 1.5h |\n180: | **Total** | **49** | **20.0h** |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n185: \n186: - [ ] `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` — MetadataService implementation\n187: - [ ] `agentcube/services/storage_interface.py` — Storage interface\n188: - [ ] `agentcube/models/metadata.py` — Pydantic data models\n189: - [ ] `agentcube/exceptions/metadata.py` — Custom exceptions\n190: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_metadata_service.py` — Unit tests\n191: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_metadata_service.py` — Integration tests\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## Verification Commands\n196: \n197: ```bash\n198: # Install verification\n199: pip install -e \".[dev,test]\"\n200: \n201: # Import verification\n202: python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService\"\n203: \n204: # Unit test verification\n205: pytest tests/unit/test_metadata_service.py -v\n206: \n207: # Integration tests\n208: pytest tests/integration/test_metadata_service.py -v\n209: \n210: # Coverage report\n211: pytest --cov=agentcube.services.metadata_service --cov-report=term-missing\n212: \n213: # Lint verification\n214: ruff check agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n215: mypy agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## Definition of Done\n221: \n222: - [ ] All 49 tasks complete\n223: - [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n224: - [ ] MetadataService importable from `agentcube.services`\n225: - [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n226: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n227: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n228: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n229: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already in pyproject.toml)\n236: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n237: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting (already present)\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: *AR-025 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-025\n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-1 (Initialized)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `MetadataService` class provides a unified, high-level interface for managing agent metadata and data models within the AgentCube CLI. This service abstracts storage operations, provides schema validation, versioning support, and enables agent discovery and configuration management.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.1 — Core Service Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775900310647,"end":1775900310696}}}}
