{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900319113,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be85163001eBe8Lk7VWH0voT","messageID":"msg_d7be83cdd0015g2pJRF7XOgzaf","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService and Data Models — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document provides technical implementation details for the `MetadataService` and data models in the AgentCube CLI project. The MetadataService provides persistent storage and validation for agent configuration using YAML files with Pydantic models, while MetadataOptions provides a dataclass for CLI option handling.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-025  \n8: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n9: **Language:** Python  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### Component Diagram\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                            CLI Layer                                          │\n21: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n22: │  │   pack command      │    │   build command     │                         │\n23: │  │   (main.py)         │    │   (main.py)         │                         │\n24: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n25: │             │                          │                                     │\n26: │             ▼                          ▼                                     │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n28: │  │   PackRuntime       │    │   BuildRuntime      │                         │\n29: │  │   (pack_runtime)    │    │   (build_runtime)   │                         │\n30: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n31: └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n32:               │                          │\n33:               ▼                          ▼\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │                       Service & Model Layer                                   │\n36: │                                                                              │\n37: │    ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐        │\n38: │    │                    MetadataService                            │        │\n39: │    │                  (metadata_service)                           │        │\n40: │    └──────────────┬────────────────────────────────┬───────────────┘        │\n41: │                   │                                │                        │\n42: │                   ▼                                ▼                        │\n43: │    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n44: │    │    AgentMetadata    │          │   MetadataOptions   │                │\n45: │    │   (Pydantic Model)  │          │     (Dataclass)     │                │\n46: │    └──────────┬──────────┘          └──────────┬──────────┘                │\n47: │               │                                │                            │\n48: │               ▼                                ▼                            │\n49: │    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n50: │    │  agent_metadata.yaml│          │  CLI Option Mapping │                │\n51: │    │  (YAML Persistence) │          │  (Runtime Options)  │                │\n52: │    └─────────────────────┘          └─────────────────────┘                │\n53: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Data Flow\n57: \n58: #### Metadata Load/Save Flow\n59: ```\n60: 1. PackRuntime calls MetadataService.load_metadata()\n61: 2. Service checks for agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml\n62: 3. If not found, creates default AgentMetadata from workspace\n63: 4. CLI options are merged via _apply_option_overrides()\n64: 5. Service validates the metadata (Pydantic validation)\n65: 6. Modified metadata saved via save_metadata()\n66: 7. Written to {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml\n67: ```\n68: \n69: #### Validation Flow\n70: ```\n71: 1. MetadataService.validate_workspace() called\n72: 2. Checks workspace exists and is directory\n73: 3. Language-specific validation:\n74:    - Python: requires at least one *.py file\n75:    - Java: requires pom.xml\n76: 4. Returns True if valid, raises ValueError if invalid\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Module Structure\n82: \n83: ### File Layout\n84: \n85: | Path | Role |\n86: |------|------|\n87: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class + `AgentMetadata` model |\n88: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n89: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package marker |\n90: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for pack operations |\n91: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for build operations |\n92: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for publish operations |\n93: \n94: ### Dependencies\n95: \n96: ```\n97: MetadataService\n98:     ├── AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n99:     ├── yaml (PyYAML)\n100:     ├── pathlib (Path handling)\n101:     └── typing (Type hints)\n102: \n103: AgentMetadata\n104:     ├── pydantic (BaseModel, Field, validators)\n105:     └── typing (Optional, Dict, Any)\n106: \n107: MetadataOptions\n108:     └── dataclasses (dataclass, field)\n109: \n110: PackRuntime/BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime\n111:     └── MetadataService (for persistence)\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## Implementation Details\n117: \n118: ### 1. AgentMetadata (Pydantic Model)\n119: \n120: The `AgentMetadata` class is the core data model for agent configuration, persisted as YAML.\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n124: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n125: \n126: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n127:     \"\"\"Pydantic model for agent metadata configuration.\n128:     \n129:     This model represents the agent_metadata.yaml file structure\n130:     and provides validation for all agent configuration fields.\n131:     \"\"\"\n132:     \n133:     # Required fields\n134:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n135:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n136:     \n137:     # Fields with defaults\n138:     language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n139:     port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n140:     build_mode: str = Field(default=\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n141:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\n142:         default=\"requirements.txt\", \n143:         description=\"Python dependency file\"\n144:     )\n145:     \n146:     # Optional fields\n147:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n148:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n149:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string\")\n150:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n151:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n152:     \n153:     # Registry configuration\n154:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry URL\")\n155:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n156:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n157:     \n158:     # AgentCube URLs\n159:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Workload Manager\")\n160:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Router\")\n161:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for readiness probe\")\n162:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")\n163:     \n164:     # Runtime state\n165:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n166:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Session ID for the agent\")\n167:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n168:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"K8s deployment info\")\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### Field Validators\n172: \n173: ```python\n174:     @field_validator('language')\n175:     @classmethod\n176:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n177:         \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n178:         allowed = ['python', 'java']\n179:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n180:             raise ValueError(f'language must be one of {allowed}')\n181:         return v.lower()\n182:     \n183:     @field_validator('build_mode')\n184:     @classmethod\n185:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n186:         \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n187:         allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n188:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n189:             raise ValueError(f'build_mode must be one of {allowed}')\n190:         return v.lower()\n191:     \n192:     @field_validator('port')\n193:     @classmethod\n194:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n195:         \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n196:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n197:             raise ValueError('port must be between 1 and 65535')\n198:         return v\n199: ```\n200: \n201: #### Model Configuration\n202: \n203: ```python\n204:     class Config:\n205:         \"\"\"Pydantic configuration.\"\"\"\n206:         # Allow population by field name\n207:         populate_by_name = True\n208:         # Validate assignment\n209:         validate_assignment = True\n210:         # Extra fields forbidden\n211:         extra = 'forbid'\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### 2. MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n217: \n218: The `MetadataOptions` dataclass provides a type-safe way to pass CLI options to runtimes.\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n222: from typing import Optional\n223: \n224: @dataclass\n225: class MetadataOptions:\n226:     \"\"\"Dataclass for CLI pack options.\n227:     \n228:     This provides a structured way to pass command-line options\n229:     to PackRuntime and other components.\n230:     \"\"\"\n231:     \n232:     # Agent configuration\n233:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n234:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n235:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n236:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n237:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n238:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n239:     description: Optional[str] = None\n240:     \n241:     # AgentCube URLs\n242:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n243:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n244:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n245:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n246:     \n247:     # Registry configuration\n248:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n249:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n250:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n251:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n252:     \n253:     @classmethod\n254:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n255:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from a dictionary.\n256:         \n257:         Args:\n258:             options: Dictionary of options (typically from CLI)\n259:             \n260:         Returns:\n261:             MetadataOptions instance with values from dict\n262:         \"\"\"\n263:         # Filter to only known fields\n264:         known_fields = {f.name for f in cls.__dataclass_fields__.values()}\n265:         filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n266:         return cls(**filtered)\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### 3. MetadataService\n272: \n273: The `MetadataService` class provides CRUD operations for agent metadata with YAML persistence.\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: import yaml\n277: from pathlib import Path\n278: from typing import Dict, Any, Optional\n279: import logging\n280: \n281: class MetadataService:\n282:     \"\"\"Service class for agent metadata operations.\n283:     \n284:     Provides:\n285:     - Loading metadata from YAML files (with fallback chain)\n286:     - Saving metadata to YAML files\n287:     - Updating metadata fields\n288:     - Validating workspace structure\n289:     \"\"\"\n290:     \n291:     # Filename precedence (highest to lowest)\n292:     METADATA_FILENAMES = ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n293:     \n294:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n295:         self.verbose = verbose\n296:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n297:         if verbose:\n298:             self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n299: ```\n300: \n301: #### Load Metadata\n302: \n303: ```python\n304:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n305:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\n306:         \n307:         Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml -> agent.yaml -> metadata.yaml\n308:         If no file exists, creates default metadata from workspace.\n309:         \n310:         Args:\n311:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n312:             \n313:         Returns:\n314:             AgentMetadata instance\n315:             \n316:         Raises:\n317:             ValueError: If workspace doesn't exist or YAML is invalid\n318:         \"\"\"\n319:         self.logger.debug(f\"Loading metadata from {workspace_path}\")\n320:         \n321:         # Find metadata file\n322:         metadata_file = None\n323:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILENAMES:\n324:             candidate = workspace_path / filename\n325:             if candidate.exists():\n326:                 metadata_file = candidate\n327:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Found metadata file: {candidate}\")\n328:                 break\n329:         \n330:         if metadata_file is None:\n331:             self.logger.debug(\"No metadata file found, creating default\")\n332:             return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path)\n333:         \n334:         # Load and parse YAML\n335:         try:\n336:             with open(metadata_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n337:                 data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n338:             \n339:             self.logger.debug(f\"Loaded metadata: {data}\")\n340:             return AgentMetadata(**data)\n341:             \n342:         except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n343:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {metadata_file}: {e}\")\n344:         except Exception as e:\n345:             raise ValueError(f\"Failed to load metadata: {e}\")\n346: ```\n347: \n348: #### Save Metadata\n349: \n350: ```python\n351:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n352:         \"\"\"Save metadata to YAML file.\n353:         \n354:         Always writes to agent_metadata.yaml (canonical filename).\n355:         \n356:         Args:\n357:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n358:             metadata: AgentMetadata to save\n359:             \n360:         Raises:\n361:             ValueError: If save fails\n362:         \"\"\"\n363:         metadata_file = workspace_path / 'agent_metadata.yaml'\n364:         self.logger.debug(f\"Saving metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n365:         \n366:         try:\n367:             # Convert to dict, excluding None values\n368:             data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n369:             \n370:             # Ensure directory exists\n371:             workspace_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n372:             \n373:             # Write YAML\n374:             with open(metadata_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n375:                 yaml.dump(\n376:                     data,\n377:                     f,\n378:                     default_flow_style=False,\n379:                     indent=2,\n380:                     sort_keys=False,\n381:                     allow_unicode=True\n382:                 )\n383:             \n384:             self.logger.info(f\"Saved metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n385:             \n386:         except Exception as e:\n387:             raise ValueError(f\"Failed to save metadata: {e}\")\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Update Metadata\n391: \n392: ```python\n393:     def update_metadata(\n394:         self, \n395:         workspace_path: Path, \n396:         updates: Dict[str, Any]\n397:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n398:         \"\"\"Update metadata with new values.\n399:         \n400:         Loads existing metadata, applies updates, and saves.\n401:         \n402:         Args:\n403:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n404:             updates: Dictionary of field updates\n405:             \n406:         Returns:\n407:             Updated AgentMetadata instance\n408:         \"\"\"\n409:         self.logger.debug(f\"Updating metadata with {updates}\")\n410:         \n411:         # Load existing\n412:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n413:         \n414:         # Apply updates\n415:         for key, value in updates.items():\n416:             if hasattr(metadata, key):\n417:                 setattr(metadata, key, value)\n418:             else:\n419:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Unknown metadata field: {key}\")\n420:         \n421:         # Re-validate and save\n422:         metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata.model_dump())\n423:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n424:         \n425:         return metadata\n426: ```\n427: \n428: #### Workspace Validation\n429: \n430: ```python\n431:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n432:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\n433:         \n434:         Checks:\n435:         - Workspace exists and is a directory\n436:         - Language-specific requirements (Python: *.py files, Java: pom.xml)\n437:         \n438:         Args:\n439:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n440:             \n441:         Returns:\n442:             True if valid\n443:             \n444:         Raises:\n445:             ValueError: If validation fails\n446:         \"\"\"\n447:         self.logger.debug(f\"Validating workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n448:         \n449:         # Check workspace exists\n450:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n451:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n452:         \n453:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n454:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n455:         \n456:         # Load metadata to determine language\n457:         try:\n458:             metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n459:         except ValueError:\n460:             # No metadata, assume Python\n461:             metadata = AgentMetadata(agent_name=workspace_path.name, entrypoint=\"main.py\")\n462:         \n463:         # Language-specific validation\n464:         if metadata.language == 'python':\n465:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n466:         elif metadata.language == 'java':\n467:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n468:         \n469:         self.logger.debug(\"Workspace validation passed\")\n470:         return True\n471:     \n472:     def _validate_python_workspace(\n473:         self, \n474:         workspace_path: Path, \n475:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n476:     ) -> None:\n477:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n478:         # Check for at least one Python file\n479:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob('*.py'))\n480:         if not py_files:\n481:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n482:         \n483:         self.logger.debug(f\"Found {len(py_files)} Python files\")\n484:     \n485:     def _validate_java_workspace(\n486:         self, \n487:         workspace_path: Path, \n488:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n489:     ) -> None:\n490:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n491:         # Check for pom.xml\n492:         pom_file = workspace_path / 'pom.xml'\n493:         if not pom_file.exists():\n494:             raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n495:         \n496:         self.logger.debug(\"Found pom.xml\")\n497: ```\n498: \n499: #### Default Metadata Creation\n500: \n501: ```python\n502:     def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n503:         \"\"\"Create default metadata from workspace.\n504:         \n505:         Infers agent name from directory name and entrypoint from\n506:         discovered files.\n507:         \n508:         Args:\n509:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n510:             \n511:         Returns:\n512:             AgentMetadata with default values\n513:         \"\"\"\n514:         agent_name = workspace_path.name\n515:         \n516:         # Infer entrypoint\n517:         entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, 'python')\n518:         \n519:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n520:             agent_name=agent_name,\n521:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n522:             language='python',\n523:         )\n524:         \n525:         self.logger.debug(f\"Created default metadata: {metadata}\")\n526:         return metadata\n527:     \n528:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n529:         \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace contents.\n530:         \n531:         Args:\n532:             workspace_path: Path to workspace\n533:             language: Programming language\n534:             \n535:         Returns:\n536:             Inferred entrypoint command\n537:         \"\"\"\n538:         if language == 'python':\n539:             # Look for common entry points\n540:             for candidate in ['main.py', 'app.py', 'server.py']:\n541:                 if (workspace_path / candidate).exists():\n542:                     return f\"python {candidate}\"\n543:             # Default to main.py\n544:             return \"python main.py\"\n545:         \n546:         elif language == 'java':\n547:             # Look for main class or jar\n548:             return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n549:         \n550:         return \"\"\n551: ```\n552: \n553: ---\n554: \n555: ## Data Models\n556: \n557: ### AgentMetadata Schema\n558: \n559: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n560: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n561: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique identifier for the agent |\n562: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n563: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language (`python`/`java`) |\n564: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Exposed port (1-65535) |\n565: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy (`local`/`cloud`) |\n566: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable description |\n567: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n568: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version (e.g., `v1.0.0`) |\n569: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Image info dict |\n570: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Auth configuration |\n571: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependencies file |\n572: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Image registry URL |\n573: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n574: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n575: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent HTTP endpoint |\n576: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for Workload Manager |\n577: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for Router |\n578: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe path |\n579: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe port |\n580: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | AgentCube-assigned ID |\n581: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session identifier |\n582: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | K8s deployment status |\n583: \n584: ### MetadataOptions Schema\n585: \n586: | Field | Type | Default | CLI Option |\n587: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n588: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--agent-name` |\n589: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `\"python\"` | `--language` |\n590: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--entrypoint` |\n591: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | `--port` |\n592: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `\"local\"` | `--build-mode` |\n593: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | (inferred) |\n594: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--description` |\n595: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n596: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n597: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n598: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | (config) |\n599: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-url` |\n600: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-username` |\n601: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-password` |\n602: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (runtime) |\n603: \n604: ### YAML Output Format\n605: \n606: ```yaml\n607: agent_name: my-agent\n608: language: python\n609: entrypoint: python main.py\n610: port: 8080\n611: build_mode: local\n612: description: My AI agent\n613: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n614: version: v1.0.0\n615: registry_url: registry.example.com\n616: registry_username: \"\"\n617: registry_password: \"\"\n618: workload_manager_url: http://workload-manager:8080\n619: router_url: http://router:8080\n620: readiness_probe_path: /health\n621: readiness_probe_port: 8080\n622: agent_id: agent-abc123\n623: session_id: session-xyz789\n624: agent_endpoint: http://my-agent.default.svc.cluster.local\n625: k8s_deployment:\n626:   deployment_name: my-agent\n627:   service_name: my-agent\n628:   namespace: default\n629:   replicas: 1\n630:   node_port: 30080\n631: ```\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## Error Handling\n636: \n637: ### Error Types\n638: \n639: | Error | Exception | Description |\n640: |-------|-----------|-------------|\n641: | Workspace Not Found | `ValueError` | Workspace path doesn't exist |\n642: | Invalid Workspace | `ValueError` | Workspace is not a directory |\n643: | No Python Files | `ValueError` | Python workspace missing .py files |\n644: | No pom.xml | `ValueError` | Java workspace missing pom.xml |\n645: | Invalid YAML | `ValueError` | YAML syntax error |\n646: | Invalid Field Value | `ValueError` | Pydantic validation error |\n647: | Save Failed | `ValueError` | File write error |\n648: \n649: ### Error Patterns\n650: \n651: **Workspace Validation:**\n652: ```python\n653: if not workspace_path.exists():\n654:     raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n655: ```\n656: \n657: **YAML Loading:**\n658: ```python\n659: try:\n660:     with open(metadata_file, 'r') as f:\n661:         data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n662: except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n663:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML: {e}\")\n664: ```\n665: \n666: **Pydantic Validation:**\n667: ```python\n668: try:\n669:     metadata = AgentMetadata(**data)\n670: except ValidationError as e:\n671:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid metadata: {e}\")\n672: ```\n673: \n674: ---\n675: \n676: ## Configuration\n677: \n678: ### Environment Variables\n679: \n680: | Variable | Used For |\n681: |----------|----------|\n682: | `AGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Default Workload Manager URL |\n683: | `AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_URL` | Default Router URL |\n684: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_URL` | Default image registry URL |\n685: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | Default registry username |\n686: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | Default registry password |\n687: \n688: ### File Locations\n689: \n690: | File | Purpose |\n691: |------|---------|\n692: | `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` | Canonical metadata file (read/write) |\n693: | `{workspace}/agent.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n694: | `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n695: | `~/.agentcube/config.yaml` | User configuration (optional) |\n696: \n697: ---\n698: \n699: ## Testing Strategy\n700: \n701: ### Unit Tests\n702: \n703: 1. **AgentMetadata tests**:\n704:    - `test_valid_metadata` - Create valid metadata\n705:    - `test_language_validation` - Test language validator\n706:    - `test_build_mode_validation` - Test build_mode validator\n707:    - `test_port_validation` - Test port range validation\n708:    - `test_invalid_language` - Error on bad language\n709:    - `test_invalid_port` - Error on out-of-range port\n710:    - `test_serialization` - YAML serialization round-trip\n711: \n712: 2. **MetadataOptions tests**:\n713:    - `test_defaults` - Default values\n714:    - `test_from_options` - Create from dict\n715:    - `test_from_options_ignores_unknown` - Unknown keys ignored\n716: \n717: 3. **MetadataService tests**:\n718:    - `test_load_existing_metadata` - Load from file\n719:    - `test_load_with_fallback` - Fallback filename\n720:    - `test_load_creates_default` - Create if missing\n721:    - `test_save_metadata` - Write to file\n722:    - `test_update_metadata` - Update and save\n723:    - `test_validate_workspace_success` - Valid workspace\n724:    - `test_validate_workspace_not_exist` - Missing workspace\n725:    - `test_validate_python_no_files` - Python validation\n726:    - `test_validate_java_no_pom` - Java validation\n727: \n728: ### Mock Strategy\n729: \n730: ```python\n731: @pytest.fixture\n732: def temp_workspace(tmp_path):\n733:     \"\"\"Create a temporary workspace.\"\"\"\n734:     workspace = tmp_path / \"test-agent\"\n735:     workspace.mkdir()\n736:     (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n737:     return workspace\n738: \n739: def test_load_existing_metadata(temp_workspace):\n740:     # Create metadata file\n741:     metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n742:     metadata_file.write_text(\"\"\"\n743: agent_name: test-agent\n744: entrypoint: python main.py\n745: language: python\n746: \"\"\")\n747:     \n748:     service = MetadataService()\n749:     metadata = service.load_metadata(temp_workspace)\n750:     \n751:     assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n752:     assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n753: \n754: def test_save_metadata(temp_workspace):\n755:     service = MetadataService()\n756:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n757:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n758:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\"\n759:     )\n760:     \n761:     service.save_metadata(temp_workspace, metadata)\n762:     \n763:     # Verify file exists\n764:     metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n765:     assert metadata_file.exists()\n766:     \n767:     # Verify content\n768:     data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n769:     assert data['agent_name'] == \"test-agent\"\n770: ```\n771: \n772: ### Integration Tests\n773: \n774: 1. **Full Pack Flow**:\n775:    - Create workspace with Python files\n776:    - Run pack with options\n777:    - Verify metadata.yaml created\n778:    - Verify options applied\n779: \n780: 2. **Language Detection**:\n781:    - Python workspace detection\n782:    - Java workspace detection\n783:    - Entrypoint inference\n784: \n785: 3. **YAML Round-trip**:\n786:    - Create metadata\n787:    - Save to YAML\n788:    - Load from YAML\n789:    - Verify fields preserved\n790: \n791: ---\n792: \n793: ## Security Considerations\n794: \n795: 1. **Registry Credentials**:\n796:    - Passwords stored in metadata.yaml (workspace-local)\n797:    - Environment variables preferred for CI/CD\n798:    - Support for credential helpers\n799: \n800: 2. **File Permissions**:\n801:    - Metadata files created with user-only permissions (0o600)\n802:    - Workspace directory permissions checked\n803: \n804: 3. **Path Traversal**:\n805:    - All paths resolved relative to workspace\n806:    - No absolute path writes outside workspace\n807:    - Sanitization of agent_name for filenames\n808: \n809: 4. **Secret Redaction**:\n810:    - registry_password excluded from verbose logging\n811:    - auth dict fields masked in output\n812: \n813: ---\n814: \n815: ## Performance Characteristics\n816: \n817: | Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n818: |-----------|------------------|-------|\n819: | Load metadata | <10ms | YAML parsing |\n820: | Save metadata | <10ms | YAML serialization |\n821: | Validate workspace | <50ms | File system checks |\n822: | Create default | <5ms | In-memory only |\n823: \n824: ### Optimization Strategies\n825: \n826: 1. **Lazy Loading**: Metadata loaded only when needed\n827: 2. **Caching**: Runtime holds metadata reference\n828: 3. **Minimal I/O**: Single file read/write per operation\n829: 4. **Efficient YAML**: sort_keys=False preserves field order\n830: \n831: ---\n832: \n833: ## Dependencies\n834: \n835: ### External Dependencies\n836: \n837: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n838: |---------|---------|---------|\n839: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation and serialization |\n840: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML parsing and generation |\n841: | `dataclasses` | (builtin) | Options dataclass |\n842: \n843: ### Python Requirements\n844: \n845: ```toml\n846: [project]\n847: dependencies = [\n848:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n849:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n850:     # ... other deps\n851: ]\n852: ```\n853: \n854: ---\n855: \n856: ## References\n857: \n858: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n859: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n860: - [Pydantic Documentation](https://docs.pydantic.dev/) - Pydantic model docs\n861: - [PyYAML Documentation](https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation) - YAML library docs\n862: \n863: ---\n864: \n865: ---\n866: \n867: # AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Design Document\n868: \n869: ## Overview\n870: \n871: This document provides technical implementation details for the Kubernetes deployment providers in the AgentCube CLI project. The `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes environments using either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource.\n872: \n873: **AR:** AR-026  \n874: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n875: **Language:** Python  \n876: **Size:** M\n877: \n878: ---\n879: \n880: ## Architecture\n881: \n882: ### Provider Hierarchy\n883: \n884: ```\n885: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n886: │                         Provider Architecture                                 │\n887: │                                                                              │\n888: │  ┌──────────────────────┐              ┌──────────────────────┐            │\n889: │  │   KubernetesProvider │              │  AgentCubeProvider   │            │\n890: │  │   (Standard K8s)     │              │  (AgentRuntime CR)   │            │\n891: │  │                      │              │                      │            │\n892: │  │  • Deployment        │              │  • AgentRuntime CR   │            │\n893: │  │  • NodePort Service  │              │  • Readiness Probes  │            │\n894: │  │  • Replicas          │              │  • Session Mgmt      │            │\n895: │  │  • NodePort (opt)    │              │  • Router/WM URLs    │            │\n896: │  └──────────┬───────────┘              └──────────┬───────────┘            │\n897: │             │                                      │                        │\n898: │             └──────────────┬───────────────────────┘                        │\n899: │                            │                                                │\n900: │                            ▼                                                │\n901: │              ┌─────────────────────────┐                                    │\n902: │              │   Kubernetes Client     │                                    │\n903: │              │   (lazy initialization) │                                    │\n904: │              └─────────────────────────┘                                    │\n905: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n906: ```\n907: \n908: ### Deployment Flow\n909: \n910: ```\n911: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n912: │                     Standard K8s Deployment Flow                              │\n913: │                                                                              │\n914: │  deploy_agent()                                                             │\n915: │       │                                                                      │\n916: │       ▼                                                                      │\n917: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n918: │  │ Validate NodePort│──► ValueError (if outside 30000-32767)               │\n919: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n920: │           │                                                                  │\n921: │           ▼                                                                  │\n922: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n923: │  │ Get K8s Client   │──► RuntimeError (if k8s unavailable)                 │\n924: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n925: │           │                                                                  │\n926: │           ▼                                                                  │\n927: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n928: │  │ Ensure Namespace │──► Creates if missing                                 │\n929: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n930: │           │                                                                  │\n931: │     ┌─────┴─────┐                                                            │\n932: │     ▼           ▼                                                            │\n933: │  ┌──────┐   ┌────────┐                                                       │\n934: │  │Deploy│   │Service │──► Create/Update resources                            │\n935: │  └──────┘   └────────┘                                                       │\n936: │     │           │                                                            │\n937: │     └─────┬─────┘                                                            │\n938: │           ▼                                                                  │\n939: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n940: │  │ Return Result    │──► deployment_name, service_name, node_port, etc     │\n941: │  └──────────────────┘                                                       │\n942: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n943: ```\n944: \n945: ### AgentRuntime CR Flow\n946: \n947: ```\n948: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n949: │                     AgentRuntime CR Deployment Flow                           │\n950: │                                                                              │\n951: │  deploy_agent_runtime()                                                     │\n952: │       │                                                                      │\n953: │       ▼                                                                      │\n954: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n955: │  │ Validate URLs    │──► ValueError (if router_url or wm_url missing)      │\n956: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n957: │           │                                                                  │\n958: │           ▼                                                                  │\n959: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n960: │  │ Get K8s Client   │                                                       │\n961: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n962: │           │                                                                  │\n963: │           ▼                                                                  │\n964: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n965: │  │ Ensure Namespace │                                                       │\n966: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n967: │           │                                                                  │\n968: │           ▼                                                                  │\n969: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n970: │  │ Build CR Spec    │──► Create spec dict with env vars, probes, etc      │\n971: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n972: │           │                                                                  │\n973: │           ▼                                                                  │\n974: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n975: │  │ Apply CR         │──► Create/Update AgentRuntime via CustomObjectsApi  │\n976: │  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n977: │           │                                                                  │\n978: │           ▼                                                                  │\n979: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n980: │  │ Return Result    │──► agent_id, agent_endpoint, status                  │\n981: │  └──────────────────┘                                                       │\n982: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n983: ```\n984: \n985: ---\n986: \n987: ## Module Structure\n988: \n989: ### File Layout\n990: \n991: | Path | Role |\n992: |------|------|\n993: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n994: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n995: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Service exports |\n996: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses providers for publish |\n997: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Uses providers for invoke |\n998: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Uses providers for status |\n999: \n1000: ### Dependencies\n1001: \n1002: ```\n1003: KubernetesProvider\n1004:     ├── kubernetes (AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api)\n1005:     ├── config (load_kube_config, load_incluster_config)\n1006:     └── typing (Dict, Any, Optional)\n1007: \n1008: AgentCubeProvider\n1009:     ├── kubernetes (CustomObjectsApi)\n1010:     ├── KubernetesProvider (shared client pattern)\n1011:     └── typing (Dict, Any, Optional)\n1012: \n1013: Runtime Integration\n1014:     ├── PublishRuntime (publish command)\n1015:     ├── InvokeRuntime (invoke command)\n1016:     └── StatusRuntime (status command)\n1017: ```\n1018: \n1019: ---\n1020: \n1021: ## Implementation Details\n1022: \n1023: ### 1. KubernetesProvider\n1024: \n1025: The `KubernetesProvider` class deploys agents using standard Kubernetes resources.\n1026: \n1027: ```python\n1028: from kubernetes import client, config\n1029: from kubernetes.client.exceptions import ApiException\n1030: from pathlib import Path\n1031: from typing import Dict, Any, Optional\n1032: import logging\n1033: import time\n1034: \n1035: class KubernetesProvider:\n1036:     \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes deployments.\n1037:     \n1038:     Creates Deployment and NodePort Service resources for agent deployment.\n1039:     Supports configurable replicas, environment variables, and optional NodePort.\n1040:     \"\"\"\n1041:     \n1042:     def __init__(\n1043:         self,\n1044:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1045:         verbose: bool = False,\n1046:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1047:     ) -> None:\n1048:         \"\"\"Initialize the Kubernetes provider.\n1049:         \n1050:         Args:\n1051:             namespace: Default namespace for resources\n1052:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n1053:             kubeconfig: Path to kubeconfig file (optional)\n1054:         \"\"\"\n1055:         self.namespace = namespace\n1056:         self.verbose = verbose\n1057:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1058:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1059:         self._k8s_client = None\n1060:         \n1061:         if verbose:\n1062:             self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n1063: ```\n1064: \n1065: #### Lazy Client Initialization\n1066: \n1067: ```python\n1068:     def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any:\n1069:         \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client with config fallback.\n1070:         \n1071:         Tries to load kubeconfig from:\n1072:         1. Explicit kubeconfig path if provided\n1073:         2. Default kubeconfig location\n1074:         3. In-cluster configuration (for running inside K8s)\n1075:         \n1076:         Returns:\n1077:             Kubernetes client APIs tuple\n1078:             \n1079:         Raises:\n1080:             RuntimeError: If kubernetes library not installed or config fails\n1081:         \"\"\"\n1082:         if self._k8s_client is not None:\n1083:             return self._k8s_client\n1084:         \n1085:         try:\n1086:             from kubernetes import client, config\n1087:         except ImportError:\n1088:             raise RuntimeError(\n1089:                 \"Kubernetes client library not installed. \"\n1090:                 \"Install with: pip install kubernetes\"\n1091:             )\n1092:         \n1093:         # Try to load configuration\n1094:         try:\n1095:             if self.kubeconfig:\n1096:                 config.load_kube_config(config_file=self.kubeconfig)\n1097:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Loaded kubeconfig from {self.kubeconfig}\")\n1098:             else:\n1099:                 config.load_kube_config()\n1100:                 self.logger.debug(\"Loaded default kubeconfig\")\n1101:         except Exception:\n1102:             # Fallback to in-cluster config\n1103:             try:\n1104:                 config.load_incluster_config()\n1105:                 self.logger.debug(\"Loaded in-cluster config\")\n1106:             except Exception as e:\n1107:                 raise RuntimeError(\n1108:                     f\"Failed to load Kubernetes configuration: {e}\"\n1109:                 )\n1110:         \n1111:         # Initialize API clients\n1112:         self._k8s_client = {\n1113:             'apps': client.AppsV1Api(),\n1114:             'core': client.CoreV1Api(),\n1115:             'custom': client.CustomObjectsApi(),\n1116:         }\n1117:         \n1118:         return self._k8s_client\n1119: ```\n1120: \n1121: #### Namespace Management\n1122: \n1123: ```python\n1124:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n1125:         \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists, create if missing.\n1126:         \n1127:         Raises:\n1128:             RuntimeError: If namespace creation fails\n1129:         \"\"\"\n1130:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1131:         core_api = k8s['core']\n1132:         \n1133:         try:\n1134:             core_api.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n1135:             self.logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n1136:         except ApiException as e:\n1137:             if e.status == 404:\n1138:                 # Create namespace\n1139:                 try:\n1140:                     namespace_body = client.V1Namespace(\n1141:                         metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n1142:                     )\n1143:                     core_api.create_namespace(namespace_body)\n1144:                     self.logger.info(f\"Created namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n1145:                 except Exception as create_err:\n1146:                     raise RuntimeError(\n1147:                         f\"Failed to create namespace {self.namespace}: {create_err}\"\n1148:                     )\n1149:             else:\n1150:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to check namespace: {e}\")\n1151: ```\n1152: \n1153: #### Deploy Agent\n1154: \n1155: ```python\n1156:     def deploy_agent(\n1157:         self,\n1158:         agent_name: str,\n1159:         image_url: str,\n1160:         port: int,\n1161:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1162:         replicas: int = 1,\n1163:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1164:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1165:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1166:         \"\"\"Deploy agent as Deployment + NodePort Service.\n1167:         \n1168:         Args:\n1169:             agent_name: Name for the agent (used for resource naming)\n1170:             image_url: Container image URL\n1171:             port: Container port to expose\n1172:             entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command override\n1173:             replicas: Number of pod replicas\n1174:             node_port: Optional specific NodePort (30000-32767)\n1175:             env_vars: Optional environment variables dict\n1176:             \n1177:         Returns:\n1178:             Dict with deployment info including:\n1179:             - deployment_name, service_name, namespace\n1180:             - node_port, service_url\n1181:             - replicas, container_port\n1182:             - status: \"deployed\"\n1183:             \n1184:         Raises:\n1185:             ValueError: If node_port is outside valid range\n1186:             RuntimeError: If deployment fails\n1187:         \"\"\"\n1188:         self.logger.info(f\"Deploying agent {agent_name} to namespace {self.namespace}\")\n1189:         \n1190:         # Validate node_port if provided\n1191:         if node_port is not None:\n1192:             if not (30000 <= node_port <= 32767):\n1193:                 raise ValueError(\n1194:                     f\"NodePort must be in range 30000-32767, got {node_port}\"\n1195:                 )\n1196:         \n1197:         # Ensure namespace exists\n1198:         self._ensure_namespace()\n1199:         \n1200:         # Create deployment\n1201:         deployment_result = self._create_deployment(\n1202:             name=agent_name,\n1203:             image_url=image_url,\n1204:             port=port,\n1205:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n1206:             replicas=replicas,\n1207:             env_vars=env_vars,\n1208:         )\n1209:         \n1210:         # Create service\n1211:         service_result = self._create_service(\n1212:             name=agent_name,\n1213:             port=port,\n1214:             node_port=node_port,\n1215:         )\n1216:         \n1217:         # Build result\n1218:         result = {\n1219:             \"deployment_name\": deployment_result['name'],\n1220:             \"service_name\": service_result['name'],\n1221:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n1222:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n1223:             \"container_port\": port,\n1224:             \"node_port\": service_result['node_port'],\n1225:             \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{service_result['node_port']}\",\n1226:             \"status\": \"deployed\",\n1227:         }\n1228:         \n1229:         self.logger.info(f\"Agent {agent_name} deployed successfully\")\n1230:         return result\n1231: ```\n1232: \n1233: #### Create Deployment\n1234: \n1235: ```python\n1236:     def _create_deployment(\n1237:         self,\n1238:         name: str,\n1239:         image_url: str,\n1240:         port: int,\n1241:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n1242:         replicas: int,\n1243:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n1244:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1245:         \"\"\"Create or update Deployment resource.\n1246:         \n1247:         Args:\n1248:             name: Deployment name\n1249:             image_url: Container image\n1250:             port: Container port\n1251:             entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command\n1252:             replicas: Number of replicas\n1253:             env_vars: Environment variables\n1254:             \n1255:         Returns:\n1256:             Dict with deployment info\n1257:         \"\"\"\n1258:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1259:         apps_api = k8s['apps']\n1260:         \n1261:         # Build container spec\n1262:         container = client.V1Container(\n1263:             name=name,\n1264:             image=image_url,\n1265:             ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n1266:         )\n1267:         \n1268:         # Add entrypoint if provided\n1269:         if entrypoint:\n1270:             parts = entrypoint.split()\n1271:             container.command = [parts[0]] if parts else []\n1272:             container.args = parts[1:] if len(parts) > 1 else []\n1273:         \n1274:         # Add environment variables\n1275:         if env_vars:\n1276:             container.env = [\n1277:                 client.V1EnvVar(name=k, value=v)\n1278:                 for k, v in env_vars.items()\n1279:             ]\n1280:         \n1281:         # Build pod template\n1282:         template = client.V1PodTemplateSpec(\n1283:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(labels={\"app\": name}),\n1284:             spec=client.V1PodSpec(\n1285:                 containers=[container],\n1286:             ),\n1287:         )\n1288:         \n1289:         # Build deployment spec\n1290:         deployment_spec = client.V1DeploymentSpec(\n1291:             replicas=replicas,\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1291. Use offset=1292 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService and Data Models — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `MetadataService` and data models in the AgentCube CLI project. The MetadataService provides persistent storage and validation for agent configuration using YAML files with Pydantic models, while MetadataOptions provides a dataclass for CLI option handling.\n\n**AR:** AR-025  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            CLI Layer                                          │","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775900319078,"end":1775900319109}}}}
