{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900325991,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be86faf001WB1pHRTJsaDpBb","messageID":"msg_d7be85dc0001hdqgigRKVt0iQD","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","offset":1292},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1292:             selector={\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": name}},\n1293:             template=template,\n1294:         )\n1295:         \n1296:         # Build deployment\n1297:         deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n1298:             api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n1299:             kind=\"Deployment\",\n1300:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(\n1301:                 name=name,\n1302:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1303:                 labels={\"app\": name},\n1304:             ),\n1305:             spec=deployment_spec,\n1306:         )\n1307:         \n1308:         # Try to update first, then create\n1309:         try:\n1310:             apps_api.replace_namespaced_deployment(\n1311:                 name=name,\n1312:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1313:                 body=deployment,\n1314:             )\n1315:             self.logger.debug(f\"Updated deployment {name}\")\n1316:         except ApiException as e:\n1317:             if e.status == 404:\n1318:                 # Create new deployment\n1319:                 apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment(\n1320:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n1321:                     body=deployment,\n1322:                 )\n1323:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Created deployment {name}\")\n1324:             else:\n1325:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to create deployment: {e}\")\n1326:         \n1327:         return {\"name\": name}\n1328: ```\n1329: \n1330: #### Create Service\n1331: \n1332: ```python\n1333:     def _create_service(\n1334:         self,\n1335:         name: str,\n1336:         port: int,\n1337:         node_port: Optional[int],\n1338:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1339:         \"\"\"Create or update NodePort Service resource.\n1340:         \n1341:         Args:\n1342:             name: Service name\n1343:             port: Target container port\n1344:             node_port: Optional specific NodePort\n1345:             \n1346:         Returns:\n1347:             Dict with service info including assigned node_port\n1348:         \"\"\"\n1349:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1350:         core_api = k8s['core']\n1351:         \n1352:         # Build service spec\n1353:         service_spec = client.V1ServiceSpec(\n1354:             type=\"NodePort\",\n1355:             selector={\"app\": name},\n1356:             ports=[client.V1ServicePort(\n1357:                 port=port,\n1358:                 target_port=port,\n1359:                 node_port=node_port,\n1360:             )],\n1361:         )\n1362:         \n1363:         # Build service\n1364:         service = client.V1Service(\n1365:             api_version=\"v1\",\n1366:             kind=\"Service\",\n1367:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(\n1368:                 name=name,\n1369:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1370:                 labels={\"app\": name},\n1371:             ),\n1372:             spec=service_spec,\n1373:         )\n1374:         \n1375:         # Try to update first, then create\n1376:         try:\n1377:             core_api.replace_namespaced_service(\n1378:                 name=name,\n1379:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1380:                 body=service,\n1381:             )\n1382:             self.logger.debug(f\"Updated service {name}\")\n1383:         except ApiException as e:\n1384:             if e.status == 404:\n1385:                 # Create new service\n1386:                 created = core_api.create_namespaced_service(\n1387:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n1388:                     body=service,\n1389:                 )\n1390:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Created service {name}\")\n1391:                 # Get assigned node port\n1392:                 node_port = created.spec.ports[0].node_port\n1393:             else:\n1394:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to create service: {e}\")\n1395:         \n1396:         # Get node port if not specified\n1397:         if node_port is None:\n1398:             svc = core_api.read_namespaced_service(name, self.namespace)\n1399:             node_port = svc.spec.ports[0].node_port\n1400:         \n1401:         return {\"name\": name, \"node_port\": node_port}\n1402: ```\n1403: \n1404: #### Wait for Deployment\n1405: \n1406: ```python\n1407:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(\n1408:         self,\n1409:         name: str,\n1410:         timeout: int = 120,\n1411:     ) -> None:\n1412:         \"\"\"Wait for deployment to be ready.\n1413:         \n1414:         Args:\n1415:             name: Deployment name\n1416:             timeout: Maximum wait time in seconds\n1417:             \n1418:         Raises:\n1419:             TimeoutError: If deployment doesn't become ready within timeout\n1420:         \"\"\"\n1421:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1422:         apps_api = k8s['apps']\n1423:         \n1424:         start_time = time.time()\n1425:         while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n1426:             try:\n1427:                 deployment = apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n1428:                     name=name,\n1429:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n1430:                 )\n1431:                 \n1432:                 # Check status\n1433:                 status = deployment.status\n1434:                 if (status.updated_replicas == status.replicas and\n1435:                     status.ready_replicas == status.replicas):\n1436:                     self.logger.debug(f\"Deployment {name} is ready\")\n1437:                     return\n1438:                 \n1439:                 self.logger.debug(\n1440:                     f\"Waiting for deployment {name}: \"\n1441:                     f\"{status.ready_replicas}/{status.replicas} ready\"\n1442:                 )\n1443:                 \n1444:             except ApiException as e:\n1445:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error checking deployment status: {e}\")\n1446:             \n1447:             time.sleep(5)\n1448:         \n1449:         raise TimeoutError(\n1450:             f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\"\n1451:         )\n1452: ```\n1453: \n1454: #### Get Status\n1455: \n1456: ```python\n1457:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1458:         \"\"\"Get deployment and service status.\n1459:         \n1460:         Args:\n1461:             agent_name: Name of the agent\n1462:             \n1463:         Returns:\n1464:             Dict with deployment and service status\n1465:         \"\"\"\n1466:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1467:         apps_api = k8s['apps']\n1468:         core_api = k8s['core']\n1469:         \n1470:         result = {\n1471:             \"deployment\": None,\n1472:             \"service\": None,\n1473:         }\n1474:         \n1475:         # Get deployment status\n1476:         try:\n1477:             deployment = apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n1478:                 name=agent_name,\n1479:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1480:             )\n1481:             result[\"deployment\"] = {\n1482:                 \"name\": deployment.metadata.name,\n1483:                 \"replicas\": deployment.spec.replicas,\n1484:                 \"ready_replicas\": deployment.status.ready_replicas or 0,\n1485:                 \"updated_replicas\": deployment.status.updated_replicas or 0,\n1486:             }\n1487:         except ApiException as e:\n1488:             if e.status != 404:\n1489:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error getting deployment status: {e}\")\n1490:         \n1491:         # Get service status\n1492:         try:\n1493:             service = core_api.read_namespaced_service(\n1494:                 name=agent_name,\n1495:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1496:             )\n1497:             result[\"service\"] = {\n1498:                 \"name\": service.metadata.name,\n1499:                 \"type\": service.spec.type,\n1500:                 \"cluster_ip\": service.spec.cluster_ip,\n1501:                 \"node_port\": service.spec.ports[0].node_port if service.spec.ports else None,\n1502:             }\n1503:         except ApiException as e:\n1504:             if e.status != 404:\n1505:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error getting service status: {e}\")\n1506:         \n1507:         return result\n1508: ```\n1509: \n1510: #### Delete Agent\n1511: \n1512: ```python\n1513:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1514:         \"\"\"Delete deployment and service resources.\n1515:         \n1516:         Args:\n1517:             agent_name: Name of the agent to delete\n1518:             \n1519:         Returns:\n1520:             Dict with deletion status\n1521:         \"\"\"\n1522:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1523:         apps_api = k8s['apps']\n1524:         core_api = k8s['core']\n1525:         \n1526:         result = {\n1527:             \"status\": \"deleted\",\n1528:             \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n1529:             \"service_name\": agent_name,\n1530:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n1531:         }\n1532:         \n1533:         # Delete deployment\n1534:         try:\n1535:             apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment(\n1536:                 name=agent_name,\n1537:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1538:             )\n1539:             self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted deployment {agent_name}\")\n1540:         except ApiException as e:\n1541:             if e.status != 404:\n1542:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting deployment: {e}\")\n1543:         \n1544:         # Delete service\n1545:         try:\n1546:             core_api.delete_namespaced_service(\n1547:                 name=agent_name,\n1548:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1549:             )\n1550:             self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted service {agent_name}\")\n1551:         except ApiException as e:\n1552:             if e.status != 404:\n1553:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting service: {e}\")\n1554:         \n1555:         return result\n1556: ```\n1557: \n1558: ---\n1559: \n1560: ### 2. AgentCubeProvider\n1561: \n1562: The `AgentCubeProvider` class deploys agents using the AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n1563: \n1564: ```python\n1565: class AgentCubeProvider:\n1566:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentRuntime CR deployments.\n1567:     \n1568:     Creates and manages AgentRuntime Custom Resources for deployment\n1569:     to AgentCube-enabled Kubernetes clusters.\n1570:     \"\"\"\n1571:     \n1572:     # CRD configuration\n1573:     CRD_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n1574:     CRD_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n1575:     CRD_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n1576:     \n1577:     def __init__(\n1578:         self,\n1579:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1580:         verbose: bool = False,\n1581:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1582:     ) -> None:\n1583:         \"\"\"Initialize the AgentCube provider.\n1584:         \n1585:         Args:\n1586:             namespace: Default namespace for resources\n1587:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n1588:             kubeconfig: Path to kubeconfig file (optional)\n1589:         \"\"\"\n1590:         self.namespace = namespace\n1591:         self.verbose = verbose\n1592:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1593:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1594:         self._k8s_client = None\n1595:         \n1596:         if verbose:\n1597:             self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n1598: ```\n1599: \n1600: #### Deploy Agent Runtime\n1601: \n1602: ```python\n1603:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n1604:         self,\n1605:         agent_name: str,\n1606:         image_url: str,\n1607:         port: int,\n1608:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1609:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1610:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1611:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1612:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n1613:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1614:         session_timeout: str = \"15m\",\n1615:         max_session_duration: str = \"8h\",\n1616:         image_pull_secrets: Optional[list] = None,\n1617:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1618:         \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n1619:         \n1620:         Args:\n1621:             agent_name: Name for the agent\n1622:             image_url: Container image URL\n1623:             port: Container port\n1624:             entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command\n1625:             env_vars: Environment variables\n1626:             workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n1627:             router_url: Router URL\n1628:             readiness_probe_path: Path for readiness probe\n1629:             readiness_probe_port: Port for readiness probe\n1630:             session_timeout: Session timeout duration\n1631:             max_session_duration: Maximum session duration\n1632:             image_pull_secrets: List of image pull secret names\n1633:             \n1634:         Returns:\n1635:             Dict with deployment info including:\n1636:             - agent_id, agent_endpoint, status\n1637:             - name, namespace\n1638:             - workload_manager_url, router_url\n1639:             \n1640:         Raises:\n1641:             ValueError: If required URLs are missing\n1642:             RuntimeError: If deployment fails\n1643:         \"\"\"\n1644:         self.logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n1645:         \n1646:         # Validate required URLs\n1647:         if not workload_manager_url or not router_url:\n1648:             raise ValueError(\n1649:                 \"AgentRuntime deployment requires both \"\n1650:                 \"workload_manager_url and router_url\"\n1651:             )\n1652:         \n1653:         # Ensure namespace exists\n1654:         self._ensure_namespace()\n1655:         \n1656:         # Build CR spec\n1657:         cr_spec = self._build_agent_runtime_spec(\n1658:             agent_name=agent_name,\n1659:             image_url=image_url,\n1660:             port=port,\n1661:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n1662:             env_vars=env_vars,\n1663:             workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n1664:             router_url=router_url,\n1665:             readiness_probe_path=readiness_probe_path,\n1666:             readiness_probe_port=readiness_probe_port,\n1667:             session_timeout=session_timeout,\n1668:             max_session_duration=max_session_duration,\n1669:             image_pull_secrets=image_pull_secrets,\n1670:         )\n1671:         \n1672:         # Apply CR\n1673:         result = self._apply_agent_runtime_cr(agent_name, cr_spec)\n1674:         \n1675:         # Add metadata to result\n1676:         result.update({\n1677:             \"agent_id\": agent_name,\n1678:             \"agent_endpoint\": f\"{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{self.namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\",\n1679:             \"workload_manager_url\": workload_manager_url,\n1680:             \"router_url\": router_url,\n1681:             \"status\": \"deployed\",\n1682:         })\n1683:         \n1684:         self.logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} deployed successfully\")\n1685:         return result\n1686: ```\n1687: \n1688: #### Build CR Spec\n1689: \n1690: ```python\n1691:     def _build_agent_runtime_spec(\n1692:         self,\n1693:         agent_name: str,\n1694:         image_url: str,\n1695:         port: int,\n1696:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n1697:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n1698:         workload_manager_url: str,\n1699:         router_url: str,\n1700:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str],\n1701:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int],\n1702:         session_timeout: str,\n1703:         max_session_duration: str,\n1704:         image_pull_secrets: Optional[list],\n1705:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1706:         \"\"\"Build AgentRuntime CR specification.\n1707:         \n1708:         Returns:\n1709:             Dict with AgentRuntime spec\n1710:         \"\"\"\n1711:         # Build environment variables\n1712:         env = []\n1713:         if env_vars:\n1714:             env.extend([{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in env_vars.items()])\n1715:         \n1716:         # Add required AgentCube env vars\n1717:         env.extend([\n1718:             {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n1719:             {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n1720:         ])\n1721:         \n1722:         # Build container spec\n1723:         container = {\n1724:             \"name\": agent_name,\n1725:             \"image\": image_url,\n1726:             \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n1727:             \"env\": env,\n1728:         }\n1729:         \n1730:         # Add entrypoint if provided\n1731:         if entrypoint:\n1732:             parts = entrypoint.split()\n1733:             container[\"command\"] = [parts[0]] if parts else []\n1734:             if len(parts) > 1:\n1735:                 container[\"args\"] = parts[1:]\n1736:         \n1737:         # Add readiness probe if configured\n1738:         if readiness_probe_path:\n1739:             container[\"readinessProbe\"] = {\n1740:                 \"httpGet\": {\n1741:                     \"path\": readiness_probe_path,\n1742:                     \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n1743:                 },\n1744:                 \"initialDelaySeconds\": 10,\n1745:                 \"periodSeconds\": 5,\n1746:             }\n1747:         \n1748:         # Build pod template\n1749:         pod_spec = {\n1750:             \"containers\": [container],\n1751:         }\n1752:         \n1753:         # Add image pull secrets\n1754:         if image_pull_secrets:\n1755:             pod_spec[\"imagePullSecrets\"] = [\n1756:                 {\"name\": secret} for secret in image_pull_secrets\n1757:             ]\n1758:         else:\n1759:             # Default secret\n1760:             pod_spec[\"imagePullSecrets\"] = [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]\n1761:         \n1762:         # Build AgentRuntime spec\n1763:         spec = {\n1764:             \"image\": image_url,\n1765:             \"port\": port,\n1766:             \"sessionTimeout\": session_timeout,\n1767:             \"maxSessionDuration\": max_session_duration,\n1768:             \"podTemplate\": {\n1769:                 \"spec\": pod_spec,\n1770:             },\n1771:         }\n1772:         \n1773:         return spec\n1774: ```\n1775: \n1776: #### Apply CR\n1777: \n1778: ```python\n1779:     def _apply_agent_runtime_cr(\n1780:         self,\n1781:         agent_name: str,\n1782:         cr_spec: Dict[str, Any],\n1783:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1784:         \"\"\"Apply AgentRuntime CR using CustomObjectsApi.\n1785:         \n1786:         Args:\n1787:             agent_name: Name for the CR\n1788:             cr_spec: CR specification\n1789:             \n1790:         Returns:\n1791:             Dict with CR info\n1792:         \"\"\"\n1793:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1794:         custom_api = k8s['custom']\n1795:         \n1796:         # Build CR body\n1797:         cr_body = {\n1798:             \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CRD_GROUP}/{self.CRD_VERSION}\",\n1799:             \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n1800:             \"metadata\": {\n1801:                 \"name\": agent_name,\n1802:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n1803:                 \"labels\": {\"app\": agent_name},\n1804:             },\n1805:             \"spec\": cr_spec,\n1806:         }\n1807:         \n1808:         # Try to get existing CR\n1809:         try:\n1810:             existing = custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n1811:                 group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n1812:                 version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n1813:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1814:                 plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n1815:                 name=agent_name,\n1816:             )\n1817:             \n1818:             # Update existing CR\n1819:             custom_api.replace_namespaced_custom_object(\n1820:                 group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n1821:                 version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n1822:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1823:                 plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n1824:                 name=agent_name,\n1825:                 body=cr_body,\n1826:             )\n1827:             self.logger.debug(f\"Updated AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n1828:             \n1829:         except ApiException as e:\n1830:             if e.status == 404:\n1831:                 # Create new CR\n1832:                 custom_api.create_namespaced_custom_object(\n1833:                     group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n1834:                     version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n1835:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n1836:                     plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n1837:                     body=cr_body,\n1838:                 )\n1839:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Created AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n1840:             else:\n1841:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n1842:         \n1843:         return {\"name\": agent_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n1844: ```\n1845: \n1846: #### Get Status\n1847: \n1848: ```python\n1849:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1850:         \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime CR status.\n1851:         \n1852:         Args:\n1853:             agent_name: Name of the AgentRuntime\n1854:             \n1855:         Returns:\n1856:             Dict with CR status\n1857:         \"\"\"\n1858:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1859:         custom_api = k8s['custom']\n1860:         \n1861:         try:\n1862:             cr = custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n1863:                 group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n1864:                 version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n1865:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1866:                 plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n1867:                 name=agent_name,\n1868:             )\n1869:             \n1870:             status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n1871:             return {\n1872:                 \"name\": agent_name,\n1873:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n1874:                 \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n1875:                 \"agent_endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\"),\n1876:                 \"conditions\": status.get(\"conditions\", []),\n1877:             }\n1878:             \n1879:         except ApiException as e:\n1880:             if e.status == 404:\n1881:                 return {\"name\": agent_name, \"status\": \"not_found\"}\n1882:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to get AgentRuntime status: {e}\")\n1883: ```\n1884: \n1885: #### Delete Agent\n1886: \n1887: ```python\n1888:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1889:         \"\"\"Delete AgentRuntime CR.\n1890:         \n1891:         Args:\n1892:             agent_name: Name of the AgentRuntime to delete\n1893:             \n1894:         Returns:\n1895:             Dict with deletion status\n1896:         \"\"\"\n1897:         k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n1898:         custom_api = k8s['custom']\n1899:         \n1900:         try:\n1901:             custom_api.delete_namespaced_custom_object(\n1902:                 group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n1903:                 version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n1904:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n1905:                 plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n1906:                 name=agent_name,\n1907:             )\n1908:             self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n1909:             \n1910:         except ApiException as e:\n1911:             if e.status != 404:\n1912:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n1913:         \n1914:         return {\n1915:             \"status\": \"deleted\",\n1916:             \"name\": agent_name,\n1917:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n1918:         }\n1919: ```\n1920: \n1921: ---\n1922: \n1923: ## Data Models\n1924: \n1925: ### KubernetesProvider Deployment Result\n1926: \n1927: | Field | Type | Description |\n1928: |-------|------|-------------|\n1929: | `deployment_name` | `str` | Name of the Deployment resource |\n1930: | `service_name` | `str` | Name of the Service resource |\n1931: | `namespace` | `str` | Deployment namespace |\n1932: | `replicas` | `int` | Number of pod replicas |\n1933: | `container_port` | `int` | Container port exposed |\n1934: | `node_port` | `int` | Assigned NodePort (30000-32767) |\n1935: | `service_url` | `str` | Service access URL |\n1936: | `status` | `str` | Deployment status (`\"deployed\"`) |\n1937: \n1938: ### AgentCubeProvider Deployment Result\n1939: \n1940: | Field | Type | Description |\n1941: |-------|------|-------------|\n1942: | `agent_id` | `str` | Agent identifier |\n1943: | `agent_endpoint` | `str` | Agent invocation endpoint |\n1944: | `name` | `str` | CR name |\n1945: | `namespace` | `str` | CR namespace |\n1946: | `status` | `str` | Deployment status (`\"deployed\"`) |\n1947: | `workload_manager_url` | `str` | Workload Manager URL |\n1948: | `router_url` | `str` | Router URL |\n1949: \n1950: ### AgentRuntime CR Spec\n1951: \n1952: ```yaml\n1953: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1954: kind: AgentRuntime\n1955: metadata:\n1956:   name: {agent_name}\n1957:   namespace: {namespace}\n1958: spec:\n1959:   image: {image_url}\n1960:   port: {port}\n1961:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n1962:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n1963:   podTemplate:\n1964:     spec:\n1965:       imagePullSecrets:\n1966:         - name: default-secret\n1967:       containers:\n1968:         - name: {agent_name}\n1969:           image: {image_url}\n1970:           ports:\n1971:             - containerPort: {port}\n1972:           env:\n1973:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n1974:               value: {workload_manager_url}\n1975:             - name: ROUTER_URL\n1976:               value: {router_url}\n1977:           command: [{command}]\n1978:           args: [{args}]\n1979:           readinessProbe:\n1980:             httpGet:\n1981:               path: {readiness_probe_path}\n1982:               port: {readiness_probe_port}\n1983:             initialDelaySeconds: 10\n1984:             periodSeconds: 5\n1985: ```\n1986: \n1987: ---\n1988: \n1989: ## Error Handling\n1990: \n1991: ### Error Types\n1992: \n1993: | Error | Exception | Description |\n1994: |-------|-----------|-------------|\n1995: | K8s Library Missing | `RuntimeError` | kubernetes package not installed |\n1996: | K8s Config Failed | `RuntimeError` | Could not load kubeconfig |\n1997: | Invalid NodePort | `ValueError` | Outside 30000-32767 range |\n1998: | Missing URLs | `ValueError` | router_url or workload_manager_url missing |\n1999: | Deployment Failed | `RuntimeError` | API error during deployment |\n2000: | Timeout | `TimeoutError` | Deployment not ready within timeout |\n2001: | CR Not Found | Returns dict | `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` |\n2002: \n2003: ### Error Patterns\n2004: \n2005: **K8s Library Check:**\n2006: ```python\n2007: try:\n2008:     from kubernetes import client, config\n2009: except ImportError:\n2010:     raise RuntimeError(\"Kubernetes client library not installed\")\n2011: ```\n2012: \n2013: **Config Loading:**\n2014: ```python\n2015: try:\n2016:     config.load_kube_config()\n2017: except Exception:\n2018:     try:\n2019:         config.load_incluster_config()\n2020:     except Exception as e:\n2021:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to load K8s configuration: {e}\")\n2022: ```\n2023: \n2024: **API Error Handling:**\n2025: ```python\n2026: try:\n2027:     api.create_namespaced_deployment(...)\n2028: except ApiException as e:\n2029:     if e.status == 404:\n2030:         # Handle not found\n2031:     else:\n2032:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Deployment failed: {e}\")\n2033: ```\n2034: \n2035: ---\n2036: \n2037: ## Configuration\n2038: \n2039: ### Environment Variables\n2040: \n2041: | Variable | Used For |\n2042: |----------|----------|\n2043: | `KUBECONFIG` | Path to kubeconfig file |\n2044: | `AGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Default Workload Manager URL |\n2045: | `AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_URL` | Default Router URL |\n2046: \n2047: ### Provider Parameters\n2048: \n2049: **KubernetesProvider:**\n2050: - `namespace`: Target namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n2051: - `verbose`: Enable debug logging (default: `False`)\n2052: - `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n2053: \n2054: **AgentCubeProvider:**\n2055: - `namespace`: Target namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n2056: - `verbose`: Enable debug logging (default: `False`)\n2057: - `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n2058: \n2059: ---\n2060: \n2061: ## Testing Strategy\n2062: \n2063: ### Unit Tests\n2064: \n2065: 1. **KubernetesProvider tests**:\n2066:    - `test_init` - Provider initialization\n2067:    - `test_get_k8s_client_lazy` - Lazy loading\n2068:    - `test_ensure_namespace_create` - Namespace creation\n2069:    - `test_deploy_agent_success` - Successful deployment\n2070:    - `test_deploy_agent_invalid_nodeport` - NodePort validation\n2071:    - `test_wait_for_deployment_ready` - Readiness polling\n2072:    - `test_wait_for_deployment_timeout` - Timeout handling\n2073:    - `test_get_agent_status` - Status retrieval\n2074:    - `test_delete_agent` - Resource deletion\n2075: \n2076: 2. **AgentCubeProvider tests**:\n2077:    - `test_init` - Provider initialization\n2078:    - `test_deploy_agent_runtime_success` - CR deployment\n2079:    - `test_deploy_agent_runtime_missing_urls` - URL validation\n2080:    - `test_build_agent_runtime_spec` - Spec building\n2081:    - `test_apply_agent_runtime_cr` - CR application\n2082:    - `test_get_agent_status` - CR status retrieval\n2083:    - `test_delete_agent` - CR deletion\n2084: \n2085: ### Integration Tests\n2086: \n2087: 1. **Full Deploy Flow**:\n2088:    - Initialize provider\n2089:    - Deploy agent\n2090:    - Verify resources created\n2091:    - Check status\n2092:    - Delete and cleanup\n2093: \n2094: 2. **AgentRuntime CR Flow**:\n2095:    - Deploy AgentRuntime\n2096:    - Verify CR created\n2097:    - Check status endpoint\n2098:    - Delete CR\n2099: \n2100: ---\n2101: \n2102: ## Security Considerations\n2103: \n2104: 1. **Kubeconfig Security**:\n2105:    - Respect kubeconfig file permissions\n2106:    - Support explicit kubeconfig path\n2107:    - No hardcoded credentials\n2108: \n2109: 2. **RBAC Compliance**:\n2110:    - Requires Deployment/Service CRUD permissions\n2111:    - Requires AgentRuntime CRUD permissions (for AgentCubeProvider)\n2112:    - Namespace-scoped operations\n2113: \n2114: 3. **Secret Handling**:\n2115:    - Image pull secrets referenced, not embedded\n2116:    - Environment variables for sensitive URLs\n2117:    - No credential logging\n2118: \n2119: 4. **Resource Isolation**:\n2120:    - Namespace isolation\n2121:    - Label-based selectors\n2122:    - Sanitized resource names\n2123: \n2124: ---\n2125: \n2126: ## Performance Characteristics\n2127: \n2128: | Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n2129: |-----------|------------------|-------|\n2130: | Client Init | ~500ms | One-time per provider |\n2131: | Deploy | ~2-5s | API calls + resource creation |\n2132: | Wait Ready | ~10-60s | Depends on image pull |\n2133: | Get Status | ~100ms | Single API call |\n2134: | Delete | ~1-2s | Resource cleanup |\n2135: \n2136: ### Optimization Strategies\n2137: \n2138: 1. **Lazy Client**: K8s client initialized once, cached\n2139: 2. **Create-or-Update**: Single code path for both operations\n2140: 3. **Timeout Config**: Configurable timeouts\n2141: 4. **Graceful Degradation**: 404 errors handled gracefully\n2142: \n2143: ---\n2144: \n2145: ## Dependencies\n2146: \n2147: ### External Dependencies\n2148: \n2149: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n2150: |---------|---------|---------|\n2151: | `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes Python client |\n2152: | `urllib3` | (dependency) | HTTP client |\n2153: | `pyyaml` | (dependency) | YAML parsing |\n2154: \n2155: ### Python Requirements\n2156: \n2157: ```toml\n2158: [project.optional-dependencies]\n2159: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n2160: dev = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\", ...]\n2161: test = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\", ...]\n2162: ```\n2163: \n2164: ---\n2165: \n2166: ## References\n2167: \n2168: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n2169: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n2170: - [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md) - AgentRuntime CR API\n2171: - [Kubernetes Python Client](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python) - Official docs\n2172: - [Kubernetes Deployment](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/) - K8s concepts\n2173: - [Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/) - CRDs\n2174: - AR-025 — MetadataService (prerequisite)\n2175: - AR-020-024 — CLI Commands (use providers)\n2176: \n2177: ---\n2178: \n2179: *AR-026 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 2179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            selector={\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": name}},\n            template=template,\n        )\n        \n        # Build deployment\n        deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n            api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n            kind=\"Deployment\",\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                labels={\"app\": name},\n            ),\n            spec=deployment_spec,\n        )\n        \n        # Try to update first, then create\n        try:\n            apps_api.replace_namespaced_deployment(\n                name=name,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775900325946,"end":1775900325986}}}}
