 ] `tests/test_metadata_integration.py` — Integration tests\n299: \n300: ### Package Files\n301: - [ ] `agentcube/services/__init__.py` — Service exports\n302: - [ ] `agentcube/models/__init__.py` — Model exports\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## Definition of Done\n307: \n308: - [ ] All 75 tasks complete\n309: - [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n310: - [ ] All integration tests pass\n311: - [ ] Type checker (mypy) clean\n312: - [ ] Linter (ruff) clean\n313: - [ ] Imports work correctly\n314: - [ ] AgentMetadata validates all fields\n315: - [ ] MetadataService loads/saves/updates YAML correctly\n316: - [ ] Workspace validation works for Python and Java\n317: - [ ] Default metadata creation infers from workspace\n\n(End of file - total 317 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService and Data Models\n\n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — AgentMetadata Model Enhancement\n\n### Tasks\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Add `model_config` to `AgentMetadata` with `populate_by_name=True`, `validate_assignment=True`, `extra='forbid'` | Unit test: extra fields raise ValidationError | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Add field `pack_timestamp: Optional[str]` with description \"ISO timestamp of pack operation\" | Unit test: field serializes/deserializes correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Add field `dockerfile_generated: Optional[bool]` with description \"Whether Dockerfile was generated\" | Unit test: field serializes/deserializes correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Verify `language` validator accepts lowercase/uppercase, rejects invalid values | Unit test: \"Python\"→\"python\", \"invalid\" raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Verify `build_mode` validator accepts lowercase/uppercase, rejects invalid values | Unit test: \"Local\"→\"local\", \"invalid\" raises ValueError | 0.5h |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775900332469,"end":1775900332489}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775900332523,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be891cb001zaLtKyh0PHFjsh","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7be87895001vogKkSs7J2jENx","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":44677,"input":4,"output":197,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":8645,"read":35831}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775900343237,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be8bbc10019eyP2eAQmyeuzk","messageID":"msg_d7be89205001oLVBFkuSmiAZlQ","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900360482,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be8ccd1001tfSFW4PXxCSaNs","messageID":"msg_d7be89205001oLVBFkuSmiAZlQ","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-026  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n10: \n11: This delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Initialize with default namespace\n22: - **GIVEN** no namespace is provided\n23: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Initialize with custom namespace\n27: - **GIVEN** `namespace=\"my-namespace\"`, `verbose=True`, and `kubeconfig=\"/path/to/kubeconfig\"`\n28: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(...)` is instantiated\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL store these values and configure the Kubernetes client accordingly\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Initialize with kubeconfig from environment\n32: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is `None` and environment variable `KUBECONFIG` is set\n33: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubernetes client with default configuration (likely from `~/.kube/config` or in-cluster config)\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Verbose logging during initialization\n37: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n38: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL log initialization details including namespace configuration\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Namespace Management\n44: \n45: The system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before deploying resources.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n48: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"my-namespace\"` already exists in the cluster\n49: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL not raise an error and continue without creating the namespace again\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Namespace does not exist\n53: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"new-namespace\"` does not exist in the cluster\n54: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using the Kubernetes API\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Namespace creation failure\n58: - **GIVEN** the user lacks permission to create namespaces\n59: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` attempts to create a namespace\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ApiException` or permission error)\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Name Sanitization\n65: \n66: The system SHALL sanitize agent names to comply with Kubernetes resource naming conventions.\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Valid name passed through\n69: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n70: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my-agent\")` is called\n71: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` unchanged\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Uppercase letters converted to lowercase\n74: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My-Agent\"`\n75: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My-Agent\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` (lowercase)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Invalid characters replaced\n79: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my_agent@v1.0\"`\n80: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my_agent@v1.0\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL return a sanitized version with invalid characters replaced or removed\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Long names truncated\n84: - **GIVEN** an agent name exceeding 63 characters (Kubernetes DNS label limit)\n85: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name()` is called\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL truncate the name to comply with Kubernetes naming constraints\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deployment\n91: \n92: The system SHALL deploy agents as Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with minimal configuration\n95: - **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `image_url=\"hello:v1.0.0\"`, `port=8080`\n96: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Ensure namespace exists\n99:   2. Create a Deployment with the specified image and port\n100:   3. Create a NodePort Service exposing the port\n101:   4. Return deployment info including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with custom entrypoint\n104: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python /app/main.py\"` and other required parameters\n105: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n106: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL include the entrypoint as the container command\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with multiple replicas\n109: - **GIVEN** `replicas=3` and other required parameters\n110: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n111: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL specify `replicas: 3`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with specific NodePort\n114: - **GIVEN** `node_port=30080` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n115: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n116: - **THEN** the Service SHALL use the specified NodePort, and `service_url` SHALL be `\"http://localhost:30080\"`\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with auto-assigned NodePort\n119: - **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n120: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n121: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort in range 30000-32767, and the returned `service_url` SHALL reflect the assigned port\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with environment variables\n124: - **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"LOG_LEVEL\": \"debug\", \"ENV\": \"production\"}`\n125: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n126: - **THEN** the Deployment container SHALL include the specified environment variables\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Deploy when Deployment already exists\n129: - **GIVEN** a Deployment with the same name already exists\n130: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL update/patch the existing Deployment with new configuration (e.g., new image)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Resource Creation\n136: \n137: The system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes Deployment resources.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Create deployment with defaults\n140: - **GIVEN** minimal required parameters\n141: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(name, image_url, port, None, 1, None)` is called\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Deployment configuration dict with:\n143:   - `apiVersion: apps/v1`\n144:   - `kind: Deployment`\n145:   - Proper selector labels matching the agent name\n146:   - Container specification with the image and port\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Create deployment with entrypoint\n149: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python main.py\"`\n150: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n151: - **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"command\": [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Create deployment with replicas\n154: - **GIVEN** `replicas=5`\n155: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n156: - **THEN** the spec SHALL include `\"replicas\": 5`\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Create deployment with env vars\n159: - **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"KEY\": \"value\"}`\n160: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n161: - **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"env\": [{\"name\": \"KEY\", \"value\": \"value\"}]`\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Service Resource Creation\n166: \n167: The system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes NodePort Service resources.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Create service with specific NodePort\n170: - **GIVEN** `port=8080`, `node_port=30080`\n171: - **WHEN** `_create_service(name=\"my-agent\", port=8080, node_port=30080)` is called\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Service configuration with:\n173:   - `type: NodePort`\n174:   - `ports` containing `port`, `targetPort`, and `nodePort`\n175:   - Selector matching the Deployment labels\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Create service with auto-assigned NodePort\n178: - **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n179: - **WHEN** `_create_service(...)` is called\n180: - **THEN** the service spec SHALL omit `nodePort`, allowing Kubernetes to auto-assign\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Service selector matches deployment\n183: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n184: - **WHEN** `_create_service(\"my-agent\", ...)` is called\n185: - **THEN** the service selector SHALL match the labels on the deployment pods\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Readiness Waiting\n190: \n191: The system SHALL wait for deployments to become ready before considering them available.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Wait for deployment succeeds\n194: - **GIVEN** a deployment that becomes ready within timeout\n195: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n196: - **THEN** it SHALL return without error once all replicas are ready\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Wait for deployment times out\n199: - **GIVEN** a deployment that fails to become ready (e.g., image pull failure)\n200: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 619. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-026  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775900360465,"end":1775900360478}}}}
