{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900518103,"sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","part":{"id":"prt_d7be91398001gObz9gMhWaI4h0","messageID":"msg_d7be8ff5b001XNGdiMQ845wyOL","sessionID":"ses_284180dcfffeQWwOBcuErq9vUW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md","content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-026\n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed) → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes environments using either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — KubernetesProvider Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` with `KubernetesProvider` class | File exists with class definition | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Implement `__init__()` with namespace, verbose, kubeconfig parameters | All parameters stored correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Add logger initialization with DEBUG level when verbose=True | Logger configured with DEBUG | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.4 | Add `_k8s_client` lazy initialization placeholder | Private attribute initialized to None | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Core provider structure defined.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — Kubernetes Client Lazy Initialization\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Implement `_get_k8s_client()` with kubernetes import check | RuntimeError if kubernetes not installed | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.2 | Implement kubeconfig loading: explicit path → default → in-cluster | Loads from provided path first | 0.5hh |\n| 4.2.3 | Implement fallback to in-cluster config when kubeconfig fails | In-cluster config loaded as fallback | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.4 | Initialize AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api, CustomObjectsApi clients | All three APIs available in dict | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.5 | Cache client in `_k8s_client` for reuse | Same client returned on subsequent calls | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.6 | Add RuntimeError with helpful message if all config methods fail | Clear error message provided | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Lazy client initialization with multiple config sources.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — Namespace Management\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Implement `_ensure_namespace()` to check namespace exists | Read namespace API call | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.2 | Create namespace if not exists (404 handling) | V1Namespace created on 404 | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.3 | Handle namespace creation failures gracefully | Appropriate error on failure | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.4 | Add debug logging for namespace operations | Logs \"exists\" vs \"created\" | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Automatic namespace management.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — KubernetesProvider Deployment Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Implement `deploy_agent()` with required parameters | Accepts agent_name, image_url, port | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Add NodePort validation (30000-32767 range) | ValueError if outside range | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.3 | Call `_ensure_namespace()` before deployment | Namespace ensured | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.4 | Call `_create_deployment()` with parameters | Deployment created | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.5 | Call `_create_service()` with parameters | Service created | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.6 | Return deployment result dict with all required fields | Contains deployment_name, service_name, namespace, replicas, container_port, node_port, service_url, status | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.7 | Add logging for deployment lifecycle | Info logs at start and success | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Full agent deployment flow.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — Deployment Resource Creation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Implement `_create_deployment()` building V1Container spec | Container with name, image, ports | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.2 | Add entrypoint parsing (split into command and args) | Command and args set correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.3 | Add environment variables as V1EnvVar list | Env vars in container spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.4 | Build V1PodTemplateSpec with labels | Template with app label | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.5 | Build V1Deployment with apps/v1 apiVersion | Proper Deployment structure | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.6 | Implement update-or-create pattern (try replace, then create) | Updates existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.7 | Handle ApiException 404 for new deployments | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.8 | Add debug logging for deployment operations | Logs \"Updated\" vs \"Created\" | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Deployment resource CRUD operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — Service Resource Creation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Implement `_create_service()` building V1ServiceSpec with NodePort type | Type set to NodePort | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Configure service ports with port, target_port, node_port | All port mappings correct | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.3 | Set selector matching deployment labels | Selector has app label | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.4 | Build V1Service with v1 apiVersion | Proper Service structure | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.5 | Implement update-or-create pattern for service | Updates existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.6 | Retrieve auto-assigned NodePort when not specified | Returns assigned port from created service | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.7 | Handle ApiException 404 for new services | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.8 | Return service result with name and node_port | Dict with correct fields | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** NodePort Service resource CRUD operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — Deployment Status & Waiting\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout parameter | Accepts timeout in seconds | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.2 | Poll deployment status every 5 seconds | time.sleep(5) between checks | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.3 | Check ready_replicas == replicas == updated_replicas | All conditions met for ready | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.4 | Add debug logging showing ready/total count | \"X/Y ready\" logged | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.5 | Raise TimeoutError if not ready within timeout | Exception raised on timeout | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.6 | Implement `get_agent_status()` returning deployment and service status | Dict with both resources | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.7 | Handle 404 errors gracefully in status check | Returns None for missing resources | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.8 | Include replica counts and node port in status | Accurate status information | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Deployment readiness monitoring and status retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — KubernetesProvider Cleanup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Implement `delete_agent()` to remove deployment | delete_namespaced_deployment called | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Implement service deletion in `delete_agent()` | delete_namespaced_service called | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Handle 404 errors gracefully during deletion | Logs warning, doesn't raise | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Return deletion status dict | Contains status, names, namespace | 0.25h |\n| 4.8.5 | Add debug logging for deletion operations | Logs \"Deleted\" messages | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Resource cleanup operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.9 — AgentCubeProvider Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.9.1 | Create `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` with `AgentCubeProvider` class | File exists with class definition | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.2 | Define CRD constants: CRD_GROUP, CRD_VERSION, CRD_PLURAL | Constants match design spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.9.3 | Implement `__init__()` with namespace, verbose, kubeconfig | Parameters stored correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.4 | Share `_k8s_client` lazy initialization pattern | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentCube provider structure.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.10 — AgentCubeProvider Deployment\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.10.1 | Implement `deploy_agent_runtime()` with all parameters | Accepts all design spec parameters | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.2 | Validate workload_manager_url and router_url are provided | ValueError if either missing | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.3 | Call `_ensure_namespace()` before deployment | Namespace ensured | 0.25h |\n| 4.10.4 | Call `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` to create CR spec | Spec dict built | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.5 | Call `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` to create/update CR | CR applied | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.6 | Return result with agent_id, agent_endpoint, status, URLs | Dict contains all fields | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.7 | Add logging for deployment lifecycle | Info logs at start and success | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR deployment flow.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.11 — AgentRuntime CR Specification Building\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.11.1 | Implement `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` | Returns spec dict | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.2 | Build environment variables including WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL | Required env vars present | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.3 | Build container spec with image, ports, env | Proper container structure | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.4 | Add entrypoint parsing (command and args) | Entrypoint split correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.5 | Add readinessProbe when readiness_probe_path provided | Probe configured with path and port | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.6 | Add imagePullSecrets (default to default-secret) | Secrets in pod spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.7 | Build full AgentRuntime spec with sessionTimeout, maxSessionDuration, podTemplate | Complete spec structure | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR specification builder.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.12 — AgentRuntime CR Application\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.12.1 | Implement `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` with name and spec | Accepts name and spec dict | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.2 | Build CR body with apiVersion, kind, metadata, spec | Proper CR structure | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.3 | Use CustomObjectsApi for CR operations | custom_api used | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.4 | Implement update-or-create pattern | Replaces existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.5 | Handle ApiException 404 for new CRs | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.6 | Add debug logging for CR operations | Logs \"Updated\" vs \"Created\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.12.7 | Return CR info dict with name and namespace | Correct return structure | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR apply operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.13 — AgentCubeProvider Status & Cleanup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.13.1 | Implement `get_agent_status()` using CustomObjectsApi | Calls get_namespaced_custom_object | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.2 | Extract status, agentEndpoint, conditions from CR | Fields correctly parsed | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.3 | Return status dict with name, namespace, status, agent_endpoint, conditions | Complete status info | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.4 | Handle 404 with {\"status\": \"not_found\"} return | Graceful not found handling | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.5 | Implement `delete_agent()` using CustomObjectsApi | delete_namespaced_custom_object called | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.6 | Handle 404 errors gracefully during deletion | Logs warning, doesn't raise | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.7 | Return deletion status dict | Contains status, name, namespace | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentRuntime status and cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.14 — Unit Tests — KubernetesProvider Initialization\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.14.1 | Write test `test_init_defaults` — default namespace, verbose, kubeconfig | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.2 | Write test `test_init_custom_values` — custom namespace, verbose=True | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.3 | Write test `test_init_logger_debug_when_verbose` — DEBUG level set | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.4 | Write test `test_k8s_client_lazy_initialization` — None until accessed | Pass | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Initialization tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.15 — Unit Tests — Kubernetes Client\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.15.1 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_import_error` — RuntimeError if kubernetes missing | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.2 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_explicit_kubeconfig` — loads from path | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.3 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_default_kubeconfig` — loads default | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.4 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_incluster_fallback` — falls back to in-cluster | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.5 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_caching` — same client returned | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.6 | Write test `test_get_k8s_client_config_error` — RuntimeError on all failures | Pass | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Kubernetes client tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.16 — Unit Tests — Namespace Management\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.16.1 | Write test `test_ensure_namespace_exists` — no-op if exists | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.16.2 | Write test `test_ensure_namespace_creates` — creates if missing | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.16.3 | Write test `test_ensure_namespace_creation_failure` — raises on error | Pass | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Namespace management tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.17 — Unit Tests — KubernetesProvider Deployment\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.17.1 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_success` — full deployment flow | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.2 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_invalid_nodeport` — ValueError if out of range | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.3 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_with_entrypoint` — entrypoint passed through | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.4 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_with_replicas` — replicas set correctly | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.5 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_with_env_vars` — env vars in container | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.6 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_with_nodeport` — specific port assigned | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.17.7 | Write test `test_deploy_agent_auto_nodeport` — auto-assigned port | Pass | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Deployment flow tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.18 — Unit Tests — Resource Creation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.18.1 | Write test `test_create_deployment_structure` — proper API objects built | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.18.2 | Write test `test_create_deployment_with_entrypoint` — command/args split | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.18.3 | Write test `test_create_deployment_update_existing` — replace on 404 | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.18.4 | Write test `test_create_service_structure` — proper Service spec | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.18.5 | Write test `test_create_service_with_nodeport` — nodePort in spec | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.18.6 | Write test `test_create_service_selector_matches` — selector labels | Pass | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Resource creation tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.19 — Unit Tests — Status & Waiting\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.19.1 | Write test `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_success` — returns when ready | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.2 | Write test `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_timeout` — TimeoutError raised | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.3 | Write test `test_get_agent_status_deployment` — deployment info returned | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.4 | Write test `test_get_agent_status_service` — service info returned | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.5 | Write test `test_get_agent_status_not_found` — handles 404 gracefully | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.6 | Write test `test_delete_agent_success` — resources deleted | Pass | 0.5h |\n| 4.19.7 | Write test `test_delete_agent_not_found` — handles 404 gr